> find an .git folder on an webserver
  > curl http://<IP or Domain>/.git/config
  > git clone http://<IP or Domain>/projects/[...]
  > ! git log !
  > git diff <commit 1> <commit 2>
  > make changes to the files
  > git status    // shows modified files
  > git add .
  > git commit -m "<String>" --author "<author name with E-Mail>"
  > git push    // specify user with password
